\@writefile{tdo}{\contentsline {todo}{\fcolorbox {black}{red!40}{\textcolor {red!40}{o}}\ REAL VULNERABILITY (Scott): This is the core of her critique: 'It is a trivial observation about network topology.' She argues I prevented entanglement via the setup itself. BUT, this is exactly my point! The network topology *is* the physical reality of the LLM substrate. If the substrate is fundamentally just isolated API calls without shared state, then it *cannot* support non-local laws. The topology defines the limits of the simulated universe!}{3}{section*.3}\protected@file@percent }
